</code><intended_behavior>Before calling `execvp`, ensure that the environment (set after `clearenv()` and `putenv()`) contains a `PATH` variable. If no `PATH` is present, set a default `PATH` (e.g., `/usr/local/sbin:/usr/local/bin:/usr/sbin:/usr/bin:/sbin:/bin`) to allow the executable to be found via `$PATH` lookup. This resolves the issue where `execvp` fails because `PATH` is empty or unset after environment clearing.</intended_behavior>, <file>src/libcrun/container.c</file>
